  <td valign=3Dtop style=3D'padding:0in 5.75pt 0in 5.75pt'>
  <p class=3DMsoNormal>Towering, fearsome reptiles with prominent horns and=
 bony
  skulls, the <span class=3DSpellE>Naxxilians</span> are somewhat draconic =
in
  appearance. They have immensely powerful forearms that equip them well for
  hand-to-hand combat.</p>
  <p class=3DMsoNormal>They are highly aggressive, but can be quite loyal a=
llies
  if befriended. <span class=3DSpellE>Naxxilians</span> tend to be extremely
  cautious, though they can be quite friendly once they become familiar with
  others.</p>
  <p class=3DMsoNormal><span class=3DSpellE>Naxxilians</span> are fanatical=
ly
  devoted to a competitive sport they call <span class=3DSpellE>Todash</spa=
n>. <span
  class=3DSpellE>Todash</span> is a game played with two small rocks. The o=
bject
  of the game is to get both rocks into the opposing team&#8217;s goal area=
 at
  the same time. A point is scored when this happens. The first team to rea=
ch
  10 points wins the game.</p>
  <p class=3DMsoNormal>In <span class=3DSpellE>Todash</span>, there are no =
strict
  rules about how you can tackle a player carrying one of the rocks, so the
  game can sometimes become rather brutal. Possession over the two rocks can
  see-saw back and forth for considerable time, with no clear advantage for
  either team. Games can sometimes stretch on for many hours, and can even =
be
  adjourned to resume the next day.</p>
  <p class=3DMsoNormal>Many <span class=3DSpellE>Naxxilians</span> live in =
small
  tribal encampments. However, they also have highly-developed urban areas,
  filled with advanced industries such as starship construction.</p>
  <p class=3DMsoNormal><span class=3DSpellE>Naxxilians</span> normally live=
 on the
  tundra wastelands of Ice Glacial planets, but can sometimes also be found=
 in
  the polar and mountain areas of Continental planets.</p>
  </td>
 </tr>
